              subtype="transcription"
              xml:id="zoor0351.transcription"
              corresp="#zoor0351.translation">
            <p>
               <choice>
                  <sic>Μνημῖον</sic>
                  <corr>Μνημεῖον</corr>
               </choice> Παύ<lb/>λου Ἀβδαλμί<lb/>θαβος, Πετρέ<lb/>ος,
                    ἠτῶν ηʹ.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation"
              ana="#b1"
              xml:id="zoor0351.translation"
              corresp="#zoor0351.transcription">
            <p>Monument of Paulus, (son) of Abdalmithabos (or Abdalmithabos, son of Paulus),
                    from Petra, (who died at the age) of 8 years</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>No date is recorded in the inscription, but it has been dated to the last quarter of the fourth century CE by other factors. The tombstone is one of about 700 discovered in Byzantine Zoora. The majority of the Greek tombstones from this location have been identified as Christian. This inscription has not been fully published. A palm branch stands below the inscription to the right. A cross-rho is found to the left of the palm branch. The text and figures are engraved.</p>
         </div>
